# Firmware Skills Agent Rules

Use this template as an always-on project instruction file when installing or developing the firmware skills.

## Core Rules

- Do not claim firmware work is complete without verification evidence and a change record.
- Do not treat build success as complete firmware validation.
- Do not silently change behavior during refactor.
- Do not ignore board, MCU, SDK, toolchain, flash/debug, RTOS, memory, timing, or hardware constraints.
- Do not overwrite user changes.
- Keep `brief/project-brief.md` current enough for a new maintainer or agent to take over.
- Use `fw-skill-governance` for any skill addition, removal, rename, trigger change, artifact schema change, terminal-status change, or user-facing workflow change.

## Required Artifact Discipline

Firmware project work should use:

```text
.codex/artifacts/firmware/
```

Skill-system maintenance should update:

```text
.codex/artifacts/firmware/skill-system/
references/skill-registry.md
CHANGELOG.md
README.md
```

## Version Discipline

- Major: breaking routing, skill names, required artifact schema, terminal status, or workflow order.
- Minor: compatible new skill, optional artifact, optional workflow branch, or skippable check.
- Patch: wording, examples, trigger clarification, or typo fixes without behavior/schema change.
